This is to note an inconsistency in break used in a foreach loop.

```
module t;
  int a[3][2];
  initial begin
    // Correct is 0,0 then ends
    // Some simulators print do 0,0 1,0 2,0
    foreach(a[i,j]) begin $display(i,j); break; end
    $finish;
  end
endmodule
```

The majority of simulators will print "0,0", but Verilator and another prints "0,0 1,0 2,0", that is it breaks only the outermost loop index. 

Therefore Verilator behavior might change at some point.
